35std::string _GetGuildEventString(GuildEvents event)
36{
37 switch (event)
38 {
39 case GE_PROMOTION:
40 return "Member promotion";
41 case GE_DEMOTION:
42 return "Member demotion";
43 case GE_MOTD:
44 return "Guild MOTD";
45 case GE_JOINED:
46 return "Member joined";
47 case GE_LEFT:
48 return "Member left";
49 case GE_REMOVED:
50 return "Member removed";
51 case GE_LEADER_IS:
52 return "Leader is";
53 case GE_LEADER_CHANGED:
54 return "Leader changed";
55 case GE_DISBANDED:
56 return "Guild disbanded";
57 case GE_TABARDCHANGE:
58 return "Tabard change";
59 case GE_RANK_UPDATED:
60 return "Rank updated";
61 case GE_RANK_DELETED:
62 return "Rank deleted";
63 case GE_SIGNED_ON:
64 return "Member signed on";
65 case GE_SIGNED_OFF:
66 return "Member signed off";
67 case GE_GUILDBANKBAGSLOTS_CHANGED:
68 return "Bank bag slots changed";
69 case GE_BANK_TAB_PURCHASED:
70 return "Bank tab purchased";
71 case GE_BANK_TAB_UPDATED:
72 return "Bank tab updated";
73 case GE_BANK_MONEY_SET:
74 return "Bank money set";
75 case GE_BANK_TAB_AND_MONEY_UPDATED:
76 return "Bank and money updated";
77 case GE_BANK_TEXT_CHANGED:
78 return "Bank tab text changed";
79 default:
80 break;
81 }
82 return "<None>";
83}

85inline uint32 _GetGuildBankTabPrice(uint8 tabId)
86{
87 switch (tabId)
88 {
89 case 0: return 100;
90 case 1: return 250;
91 case 2: return 500;
92 case 3: return 1000;
93 case 4: return 2500;
94 case 5: return 5000;
95 default: return 0;
96 }

120// LogHolder
121Guild::LogHolder::~LogHolder()
122{
123 // Cleanup
124 for (GuildLog::iterator itr = m_log.begin(); itr != m_log.end(); ++itr)
125 delete (*itr);
126}
127
128// Adds event loaded from database to collection
129inline void Guild::LogHolder::LoadEvent(LogEntry* entry)
130{
131 if (m_nextGUID == uint32(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_GUID_UNDEFINED))
132 m_nextGUID = entry->GetGUID();
133 m_log.push_front(entry);
134}
135
136// Adds new event happened in game.
137// If maximum number of events is reached, oldest event is removed from collection.
138inline void Guild::LogHolder::AddEvent(SQLTransaction& trans, LogEntry* entry)
139{
140 // Check max records limit
141 if (m_log.size() >= m_maxRecords)
142 {
143 LogEntry* oldEntry = m_log.front();
144 delete oldEntry;
145 m_log.pop_front();
146 }
147 // Add event to list
148 m_log.push_back(entry);
149 // Save to DB
150 entry->SaveToDB(trans);
151}
152
153// Writes information about all events into packet.
154inline void Guild::LogHolder::WritePacket(WorldPacket& data) const
155{
156 data << uint8(m_log.size());
157 for (GuildLog::const_iterator itr = m_log.begin(); itr != m_log.end(); ++itr)
158 (*itr)->WritePacket(data);
159}
160
161inline uint32 Guild::LogHolder::GetNextGUID()
162{
163 // Next guid was not initialized. It means there are no records for this holder in DB yet.
164 // Start from the beginning.
165 if (m_nextGUID == uint32(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_GUID_UNDEFINED))
166 m_nextGUID = 0;
167 else
168 m_nextGUID = (m_nextGUID + 1) % m_maxRecords;
169 return m_nextGUID;
170}

172// EventLogEntry
173void Guild::EventLogEntry::SaveToDB(SQLTransaction& trans) const
174{
175 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_EVENTLOG);
176 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_guildId);
177 stmt->setUInt32(1, m_guid);
178 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
179
180 uint8 index = 0;
181 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GUILD_EVENTLOG);
182 stmt->setUInt32( index, m_guildId);
183 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_guid);
184 stmt->setUInt8 (++index, uint8(m_eventType));
185 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_playerGuid1);
186 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_playerGuid2);
187 stmt->setUInt8 (++index, m_newRank);
188 stmt->setUInt64(++index, m_timestamp);
189 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
190}
191
192void Guild::EventLogEntry::WritePacket(WorldPacket& data) const
193{
194 // Event type
195 data << uint8(m_eventType);
196 // Player 1
197 data << ObjectGuid(HighGuid::Player, m_playerGuid1);
198 // Player 2 not for left/join guild events
199 if (m_eventType != GUILD_EVENT_LOG_JOIN_GUILD && m_eventType != GUILD_EVENT_LOG_LEAVE_GUILD)
200 data << ObjectGuid(HighGuid::Player, m_playerGuid2);
201 // New Rank - only for promote/demote guild events
202 if (m_eventType == GUILD_EVENT_LOG_PROMOTE_PLAYER || m_eventType == GUILD_EVENT_LOG_DEMOTE_PLAYER)
203 data << uint8(m_newRank);
204 // Event timestamp
205 data << uint32(::time(NULL) - m_timestamp);
206}

208// BankEventLogEntry
209void Guild::BankEventLogEntry::SaveToDB(SQLTransaction& trans) const
210{
211 uint8 index = 0;
212
213 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_EVENTLOG);
214 stmt->setUInt32( index, m_guildId);
215 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_guid);
216 stmt->setUInt8 (++index, m_bankTabId);
217 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
218
219 index = 0;
220 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GUILD_BANK_EVENTLOG);
221 stmt->setUInt32( index, m_guildId);
222 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_guid);
223 stmt->setUInt8 (++index, m_bankTabId);
224 stmt->setUInt8 (++index, uint8(m_eventType));
225 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_playerGuid);
226 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_itemOrMoney);
227 stmt->setUInt16(++index, m_itemStackCount);
228 stmt->setUInt8 (++index, m_destTabId);
229 stmt->setUInt64(++index, m_timestamp);
230 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
231}
232
233void Guild::BankEventLogEntry::WritePacket(WorldPacket& data) const
234{
235 data << uint8(m_eventType);
236 data << ObjectGuid(HighGuid::Player, m_playerGuid);
237
238 switch (m_eventType)
239 {
240 case GUILD_BANK_LOG_DEPOSIT_ITEM:
241 case GUILD_BANK_LOG_WITHDRAW_ITEM:
242 data << uint32(m_itemOrMoney);
243 data << uint32(m_itemStackCount);
244 break;
245 case GUILD_BANK_LOG_MOVE_ITEM:
246 case GUILD_BANK_LOG_MOVE_ITEM2:
247 data << uint32(m_itemOrMoney);
248 data << uint32(m_itemStackCount);
249 data << uint8(m_destTabId);
250 break;
251 default:
252 data << uint32(m_itemOrMoney);
253 }
254
255 data << uint32(time(NULL) - m_timestamp);
256}

280void Guild::RankInfo::CreateMissingTabsIfNeeded(uint8 tabs, SQLTransaction& trans, bool logOnCreate /* = false */)
281{
282 for (uint8 i = 0; i < tabs; ++i)
283 {
284 GuildBankRightsAndSlots& rightsAndSlots = m_bankTabRightsAndSlots[i];
285 if (rightsAndSlots.GetTabId() == i)
286 continue;
287
288 rightsAndSlots.SetTabId(i);
289 if (m_rankId == GR_GUILDMASTER)
290 rightsAndSlots.SetGuildMasterValues();
291
292 if (logOnCreate)
293 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "Guild %u has broken Tab %u for rank %u. Created default tab.", m_guildId, i, m_rankId);
294
295 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GUILD_BANK_RIGHT);
296 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_guildId);
297 stmt->setUInt8(1, i);
298 stmt->setUInt8(2, m_rankId);
299 stmt->setUInt8(3, rightsAndSlots.GetRights());
300 stmt->setUInt32(4, rightsAndSlots.GetSlots());
301 trans->Append(stmt);
302 }
303}
304
305void Guild::RankInfo::WritePacket(WorldPacket& data) const
306{
307 data << uint32(m_rights);
308 if (m_bankMoneyPerDay == GUILD_WITHDRAW_MONEY_UNLIMITED)
309 data << uint32(GUILD_WITHDRAW_MONEY_UNLIMITED);
310 else
311 data << uint32(m_bankMoneyPerDay);
312 for (uint8 i = 0; i < GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS; ++i)
313 {
314 data << uint32(m_bankTabRightsAndSlots[i].GetRights());
315 data << uint32(m_bankTabRightsAndSlots[i].GetSlots());
316 }
317}

394
395bool Guild::BankTab::LoadItemFromDB(Field* fields)
396{
397 uint8 slotId = fields[13].GetUInt8();
398 ObjectGuid::LowType itemGuid = fields[14].GetUInt32();
399 uint32 itemEntry = fields[15].GetUInt32();
400 if (slotId >= GUILD_BANK_MAX_SLOTS)
401 {
402 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "Invalid slot for item (GUID: %u, id: %u) in guild bank, skipped.", itemGuid, itemEntry);
403 return false;
404 }
405
406 ItemTemplate const* proto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(itemEntry);
407 if (!proto)
408 {
409 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "Unknown item (GUID: %u, id: %u) in guild bank, skipped.", itemGuid, itemEntry);
410 return false;
411 }
412
413 Item* pItem = NewItemOrBag(proto);
414 if (!pItem->LoadFromDB(itemGuid, ObjectGuid::Empty, fields, itemEntry))
415 {
416 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "Item (GUID %u, id: %u) not found in item_instance, deleting from guild bank!", itemGuid, itemEntry);
417
418 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_NONEXISTENT_GUILD_BANK_ITEM);
419 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_guildId);
420 stmt->setUInt8 (1, m_tabId);
421 stmt->setUInt8 (2, slotId);
422 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
423
424 delete pItem;
425 return false;
426 }
427
428 pItem->AddToWorld();
429 m_items[slotId] = pItem;
430 return true;
431}

433// Deletes contents of the tab from the world (and from DB if necessary)
434void Guild::BankTab::Delete(SQLTransaction& trans, bool removeItemsFromDB)
435{
436 for (uint8 slotId = 0; slotId < GUILD_BANK_MAX_SLOTS; ++slotId)
437 if (Item* pItem = m_items[slotId])
438 {
439 pItem->RemoveFromWorld();
440 if (removeItemsFromDB)
441 pItem->DeleteFromDB(trans);
442 delete pItem;
443 pItem = NULL;
444 }
445}
446
447inline void Guild::BankTab::WritePacket(WorldPacket& data) const
448{
449 uint8 count = 0;
450
451 size_t pos = data.wpos();
452 data << uint8(0);
453
454 for (uint8 slotId = 0; slotId < GUILD_BANK_MAX_SLOTS; ++slotId)
455 if (WriteSlotPacket(data, slotId))
456 ++count;
457
458 data.put<uint8>(pos, count);
459}
460
461// Writes information about contents of specified slot into packet.
462bool Guild::BankTab::WriteSlotPacket(WorldPacket& data, uint8 slotId, bool ignoreEmpty /* = true */) const
463{
464 Item* pItem = GetItem(slotId);
465 uint32 itemEntry = pItem ? pItem->GetEntry() : 0;
466
467 if (!itemEntry && ignoreEmpty)
468 return false;
469
470 data << uint8(slotId);
471 data << uint32(itemEntry);
472 if (itemEntry)
473 {
474 data << uint32(0); // 3.3.0 (0x00018020, 0x00018000)
475
476
477 if (uint32 random = pItem->GetItemRandomPropertyId())
478 {
479 data << uint32(random); // Random item property id
480 data << uint32(pItem->GetItemSuffixFactor()); // SuffixFactor
481 }
482 else
483 data << uint32(0);
484
485 data << uint32(pItem->GetCount()); // ITEM_FIELD_STACK_COUNT
486 data << uint32(0);
487 data << uint8(abs(pItem->GetSpellCharges())); // Spell charges
488
489 uint8 enchCount = 0;
490 size_t enchCountPos = data.wpos();
491
492 data << uint8(enchCount); // Number of enchantments
493 for (uint32 i = PERM_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT; i < MAX_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT; ++i)
494 if (uint32 enchId = pItem->GetEnchantmentId(EnchantmentSlot(i)))
495 {
496 data << uint8(i);
497 data << uint32(enchId);
498 ++enchCount;
499 }
500 data.put<uint8>(enchCountPos, enchCount);
501 }
502 return true;
503}

536// Sets/removes contents of specified slot.
537// If pItem == NULL contents are removed.
538bool Guild::BankTab::SetItem(SQLTransaction& trans, uint8 slotId, Item* item)
539{
540 if (slotId >= GUILD_BANK_MAX_SLOTS)
541 return false;
542
543 m_items[slotId] = item;
544
545 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_ITEM);
546 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_guildId);
547 stmt->setUInt8 (1, m_tabId);
548 stmt->setUInt8 (2, slotId);
549 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
550
551 if (item)
552 {
553 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GUILD_BANK_ITEM);
554 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_guildId);
555 stmt->setUInt8 (1, m_tabId);
556 stmt->setUInt8 (2, slotId);
557 stmt->setUInt32(3, item->GetGUID().GetCounter());
558 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
559
560 item->SetGuidValue(ITEM_FIELD_CONTAINED, ObjectGuid::Empty);
561 item->SetGuidValue(ITEM_FIELD_OWNER, ObjectGuid::Empty);
562 item->FSetState(ITEM_NEW);
563 item->SaveToDB(trans); // Not in inventory and can be saved standalone
564 }
565 return true;
566}
567
568void Guild::BankTab::SendText(Guild const* guild, WorldSession* session) const
569{
570 WorldPacket data(MSG_QUERY_GUILD_BANK_TEXT, 1 + m_text.size() + 1);
571 data << uint8(m_tabId);
572 data << m_text;
573
574 if (session)
575 {
576 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "MSG_QUERY_GUILD_BANK_TEXT [%s]: Tabid: %u, Text: %s"
577 , session->GetPlayerInfo().c_str(), m_tabId, m_text.c_str());
578 session->SendPacket(&data);
579 }
580 else
581 {
582 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "MSG_QUERY_GUILD_BANK_TEXT [Broadcast]: Tabid: %u, Text: %s", m_tabId, m_text.c_str());
583 guild->BroadcastPacket(&data);
584 }
585}

657// Loads member's data from database.
658// If member has broken fields (level, class) returns false.
659// In this case member has to be removed from guild.
660bool Guild::Member::LoadFromDB(Field* fields)
661{
662 m_publicNote = fields[3].GetString();
663 m_officerNote = fields[4].GetString();
664
665 for (uint8 i = 0; i <= GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS; ++i)
666 m_bankWithdraw[i] = fields[5 + i].GetUInt32();
667
668 SetStats(fields[12].GetString(),
669 fields[13].GetUInt8(), // characters.level
670 fields[14].GetUInt8(), // characters.class
671 fields[15].GetUInt16(), // characters.zone
672 fields[16].GetUInt32()); // characters.account
673 m_logoutTime = fields[17].GetUInt32(); // characters.logout_time
674
675 if (!CheckStats())
676 return false;
677
678 if (!m_zoneId)
679 {
680 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "%s has broken zone-data", m_guid.ToString().c_str());
681 m_zoneId = Player::GetZoneIdFromDB(m_guid);
682 }
683
684 ResetFlags();
685 return true;
686}
687
688// Validate player fields. Returns false if corrupted fields are found.
689bool Guild::Member::CheckStats() const
690{
691 if (m_level < 1)
692 {
693 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "%s has a broken data in field `characters`.`level`, deleting him from guild!", m_guid.ToString().c_str());
694 return false;
695 }
696
697 if (m_class < CLASS_WARRIOR || m_class >= MAX_CLASSES)
698 {
699 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "%s has a broken data in field `characters`.`class`, deleting him from guild!", m_guid.ToString().c_str());
700 return false;
701 }
702 return true;
703}

727// Decreases amount of money/slots left for today.
728// If (tabId == GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS) decrease money amount.
729// Otherwise decrease remaining items amount for specified tab.
730void Guild::Member::UpdateBankWithdrawValue(SQLTransaction& trans, uint8 tabId, uint32 amount)
731{
732 m_bankWithdraw[tabId] += amount;
733
734 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GUILD_MEMBER_WITHDRAW);
735 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_guid.GetCounter());

737 {

739 stmt->setUInt32(i, withdraw);
740 }
741
742 CharacterDatabase.ExecuteOrAppend(trans, stmt);
743}

746{
747 for (uint8 tabId = 0; tabId <= GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS; ++tabId)

749}

954Item* Guild::BankMoveItemData::StoreItem(SQLTransaction& trans, Item* pItem)
955{
956 if (!pItem)
957 return NULL;
958
959 BankTab* pTab = m_pGuild->GetBankTab(m_container);
960 if (!pTab)
961 return NULL;
962
963 Item* pLastItem = pItem;
964 for (ItemPosCountVec::const_iterator itr = m_vec.begin(); itr != m_vec.end(); )
965 {
966 ItemPosCount pos(*itr);
967 ++itr;
968
969 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "GUILD STORAGE: StoreItem tab = %u, slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u",
970 m_container, m_slotId, pItem->GetEntry(), pItem->GetCount());
971 pLastItem = _StoreItem(trans, pTab, pItem, pos, itr != m_vec.end());
972 }
973 return pLastItem;
974}

1002Item* Guild::BankMoveItemData::_StoreItem(SQLTransaction& trans, BankTab* pTab, Item* pItem, ItemPosCount& pos, bool clone) const
1003{
1004 uint8 slotId = uint8(pos.pos);
1005 uint32 count = pos.count;
1006 if (Item* pItemDest = pTab->GetItem(slotId))
1007 {
1008 pItemDest->SetCount(pItemDest->GetCount() + count);
1009 pItemDest->FSetState(ITEM_CHANGED);
1010 pItemDest->SaveToDB(trans);
1011 if (!clone)
1012 {
1013 pItem->RemoveFromWorld();
1014 pItem->DeleteFromDB(trans);
1015 delete pItem;
1016 }
1017 return pItemDest;
1018 }
1019
1020 if (clone)
1021 pItem = pItem->CloneItem(count);
1022 else
1023 pItem->SetCount(count);
1024
1025 if (pItem && pTab->SetItem(trans, slotId, pItem))
1026 return pItem;
1027
1028 return NULL;
1029}
1030
1031// Tries to reserve space for source item.
1032// If item in destination slot exists it must be the item of the same entry
1033// and stack must have enough space to take at least one item.
1034// Returns false if destination item specified and it cannot be used to reserve space.
1035bool Guild::BankMoveItemData::_ReserveSpace(uint8 slotId, Item* pItem, Item* pItemDest, uint32& count)
1036{
1037 uint32 requiredSpace = pItem->GetMaxStackCount();
1038 if (pItemDest)
1039 {
1040 // Make sure source and destination items match and destination item has space for more stacks.
1041 if (pItemDest->GetEntry() != pItem->GetEntry() || pItemDest->GetCount() >= pItem->GetMaxStackCount())
1042 return false;
1043 requiredSpace -= pItemDest->GetCount();
1044 }
1045 // Let's not be greedy, reserve only required space
1046 requiredSpace = std::min(requiredSpace, count);
1047
1048 // Reserve space
1049 ItemPosCount pos(slotId, requiredSpace);
1050 if (!pos.isContainedIn(m_vec))
1051 {
1052 m_vec.push_back(pos);
1053 count -= requiredSpace;
1054 }
1055 return true;
1056}
1057
1058void Guild::BankMoveItemData::CanStoreItemInTab(Item* pItem, uint8 skipSlotId, bool merge, uint32& count)
1059{
1060 for (uint8 slotId = 0; (slotId < GUILD_BANK_MAX_SLOTS) && (count > 0); ++slotId)
1061 {
1062 // Skip slot already processed in CanStore (when destination slot was specified)
1063 if (slotId == skipSlotId)
1064 continue;
1065
1066 Item* pItemDest = m_pGuild->_GetItem(m_container, slotId);
1067 if (pItemDest == pItem)
1068 pItemDest = NULL;
1069
1070 // If merge skip empty, if not merge skip non-empty
1071 if ((pItemDest != NULL) != merge)
1072 continue;
1073
1074 _ReserveSpace(slotId, pItem, pItemDest, count);
1075 }
1076}
1077
1078InventoryResult Guild::BankMoveItemData::CanStore(Item* pItem, bool swap)
1079{
1080 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "GUILD STORAGE: CanStore() tab = %u, slot = %u, item = %u, count = %u",
1081 m_container, m_slotId, pItem->GetEntry(), pItem->GetCount());
1082
1083 uint32 count = pItem->GetCount();
1084 // Soulbound items cannot be moved
1085 if (pItem->IsSoulBound())
1086 return EQUIP_ERR_CANT_DROP_SOULBOUND;
1087
1088 // Make sure destination bank tab exists
1089 if (m_container >= m_pGuild->_GetPurchasedTabsSize())
1090 return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_DOESNT_GO_INTO_BAG;
1091
1092 // Slot explicitely specified. Check it.
1093 if (m_slotId != NULL_SLOT)
1094 {
1095 Item* pItemDest = m_pGuild->_GetItem(m_container, m_slotId);
1096 // Ignore swapped item (this slot will be empty after move)
1097 if ((pItemDest == pItem) || swap)
1098 pItemDest = NULL;
1099
1100 if (!_ReserveSpace(m_slotId, pItem, pItemDest, count))
1101 return EQUIP_ERR_ITEM_CANT_STACK;
1102
1103 if (count == 0)
1104 return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1105 }
1106
1107 // Slot was not specified or it has not enough space for all the items in stack
1108 // Search for stacks to merge with
1109 if (pItem->GetMaxStackCount() > 1)
1110 {
1111 CanStoreItemInTab(pItem, m_slotId, true, count);
1112 if (count == 0)
1113 return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1114 }
1115
1116 // Search free slot for item
1117 CanStoreItemInTab(pItem, m_slotId, false, count);
1118 if (count == 0)
1119 return EQUIP_ERR_OK;
1120
1121 return EQUIP_ERR_BANK_FULL;
1122}

1158// Creates new guild with default data and saves it to database.
1159bool Guild::Create(Player* pLeader, std::string const& name)
1160{
1161 // Check if guild with such name already exists
1162 if (sGuildMgr->GetGuildByName(name))
1163 return false;
1164
1165 WorldSession* pLeaderSession = pLeader->GetSession();
1166 if (!pLeaderSession)
1167 return false;
1168
1169 m_id = sGuildMgr->GenerateGuildId();
1170 m_leaderGuid = pLeader->GetGUID();
1171 m_name = name;
1172 m_info = "";
1173 m_motd = "No message set.";
1174 m_bankMoney = 0;
1175 m_createdDate = ::time(NULL);
1176 _CreateLogHolders();
1177
1178 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "GUILD: creating guild [%s] for leader %s (%u)",
1179 name.c_str(), pLeader->GetName().c_str(), m_leaderGuid.GetCounter());
1180
1181 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
1182
1183 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_MEMBERS);
1184 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1185 trans->Append(stmt);
1186
1187 uint8 index = 0;
1188 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_INS_GUILD);
1189 stmt->setUInt32( index, m_id);
1190 stmt->setString(++index, name);
1191 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_leaderGuid.GetCounter());
1192 stmt->setString(++index, m_info);
1193 stmt->setString(++index, m_motd);
1194 stmt->setUInt64(++index, uint32(m_createdDate));
1195 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_emblemInfo.GetStyle());
1196 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_emblemInfo.GetColor());
1197 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_emblemInfo.GetBorderStyle());
1198 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_emblemInfo.GetBorderColor());
1199 stmt->setUInt32(++index, m_emblemInfo.GetBackgroundColor());
1200 stmt->setUInt64(++index, m_bankMoney);
1201 trans->Append(stmt);
1202
1203 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
1204 _CreateDefaultGuildRanks(pLeaderSession->GetSessionDbLocaleIndex()); // Create default ranks
1205 bool ret = AddMember(m_leaderGuid, GR_GUILDMASTER); // Add guildmaster
1206
1207 if (ret)
1208 sScriptMgr->OnGuildCreate(this, pLeader, name);
1209
1210 return ret;
1211}

1213// Disbands guild and deletes all related data from database
1214void Guild::Disband()
1215{
1216 // Call scripts before guild data removed from database
1217 sScriptMgr->OnGuildDisband(this);
1218
1219 _BroadcastEvent(GE_DISBANDED, ObjectGuid::Empty);
1220 // Remove all members
1221 while (!m_members.empty())
1222 {
1223 Members::const_iterator itr = m_members.begin();
1224 DeleteMember(itr->second->GetGUID(), true);
1225 }
1226
1227 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
1228
1229 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD);
1230 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1231 trans->Append(stmt);
1232
1233 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_RANKS);
1234 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1235 trans->Append(stmt);
1236
1237 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_TABS);
1238 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1239 trans->Append(stmt);
1240
1241 // Free bank tab used memory and delete items stored in them
1242 _DeleteBankItems(trans, true);
1243
1244 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_ITEMS);
1245 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1246 trans->Append(stmt);
1247
1248 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_RIGHTS);
1249 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1250 trans->Append(stmt);
1251
1252 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_EVENTLOGS);
1253 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1254 trans->Append(stmt);
1255
1256 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_EVENTLOGS);
1257 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1258 trans->Append(stmt);
1259
1260 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
1261 sGuildMgr->RemoveGuild(m_id);
1262}

1307void Guild::HandleRoster(WorldSession* session)
1308{
1309 // Guess size
1310 WorldPacket data(SMSG_GUILD_ROSTER, (4 + m_motd.length() + 1 + m_info.length() + 1 + 4 + _GetRanksSize() * (4 + 4 + GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS * (4 + 4)) + m_members.size() * 50));
1311 data << uint32(m_members.size());
1312 data << m_motd;
1313 data << m_info;
1314
1315 data << uint32(_GetRanksSize());
1316 for (Ranks::const_iterator ritr = m_ranks.begin(); ritr != m_ranks.end(); ++ritr)
1317 ritr->WritePacket(data);
1318
1319 for (Members::const_iterator itr = m_members.begin(); itr != m_members.end(); ++itr)
1320 itr->second->WritePacket(data, _HasRankRight(session->GetPlayer(), GR_RIGHT_VIEWOFFNOTE));
1321
1322 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "SMSG_GUILD_ROSTER [%s]", session->GetPlayerInfo().c_str());
1323 session->SendPacket(&data);
1324}

1514void Guild::HandleInviteMember(WorldSession* session, std::string const& name)
1515{
1516 Player* pInvitee = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayerByName(name);
1517 if (!pInvitee)
1518 {
1519 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_INVITE, ERR_GUILD_PLAYER_NOT_FOUND_S, name);
1520 return;
1521 }
1522
1523 Player* player = session->GetPlayer();
1524 // Do not show invitations from ignored players
1525 if (pInvitee->GetSocial()->HasIgnore(player->GetGUID().GetCounter()))
1526 return;
1527
1528 if (!sWorld->getBoolConfig(CONFIG_ALLOW_TWO_SIDE_INTERACTION_GUILD) && pInvitee->GetTeam() != player->GetTeam())
1529 {
1530 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_INVITE, ERR_GUILD_NOT_ALLIED, name);
1531 return;
1532 }
1533 // Invited player cannot be in another guild
1534 if (pInvitee->GetGuildId())
1535 {
1536 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_INVITE, ERR_ALREADY_IN_GUILD_S, name);
1537 return;
1538 }
1539 // Invited player cannot be invited
1540 if (pInvitee->GetGuildIdInvited())
1541 {
1542 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_INVITE, ERR_ALREADY_INVITED_TO_GUILD_S, name);
1543 return;
1544 }
1545 // Inviting player must have rights to invite
1546 if (!_HasRankRight(player, GR_RIGHT_INVITE))
1547 {
1548 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_INVITE, ERR_GUILD_PERMISSIONS);
1549 return;
1550 }
1551
1552 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_INVITE, ERR_GUILD_COMMAND_SUCCESS, name);
1553
1554 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "Player %s invited %s to join his Guild", player->GetName().c_str(), name.c_str());
1555
1556 pInvitee->SetGuildIdInvited(m_id);
1557 _LogEvent(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_INVITE_PLAYER, player->GetGUID().GetCounter(), pInvitee->GetGUID().GetCounter());
1558
1559 WorldPacket data(SMSG_GUILD_INVITE, 8 + 10); // Guess size
1560 data << player->GetName();
1561 data << m_name;
1562 pInvitee->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
1563 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "SMSG_GUILD_INVITE [%s]", pInvitee->GetName().c_str());
1564}

1576void Guild::HandleLeaveMember(WorldSession* session)
1577{
1578 Player* player = session->GetPlayer();
1579 bool disband = false;
1580
1581 // If leader is leaving
1582 if (_IsLeader(player))
1583 {
1584 if (m_members.size() > 1)
1585 // Leader cannot leave if he is not the last member
1586 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_QUIT, ERR_GUILD_LEADER_LEAVE);
1587 else
1588 {
1589 // Guild is disbanded if leader leaves.
1590 Disband();
1591 disband = true;
1592 }
1593 }
1594 else
1595 {
1596 DeleteMember(player->GetGUID(), false, false);
1597
1598 _LogEvent(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_LEAVE_GUILD, player->GetGUID().GetCounter());
1599 _BroadcastEvent(GE_LEFT, player->GetGUID(), player->GetName().c_str());
1600
1601 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_QUIT, ERR_GUILD_COMMAND_SUCCESS, m_name);
1602 }
1603
1604 sCalendarMgr->RemovePlayerGuildEventsAndSignups(player->GetGUID(), GetId());
1605
1606 if (disband)
1607 delete this;
1608}

1610void Guild::HandleRemoveMember(WorldSession* session, std::string const& name)
1611{
1612 Player* player = session->GetPlayer();
1613 // Player must have rights to remove members
1614 if (!_HasRankRight(player, GR_RIGHT_REMOVE))
1615 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_REMOVE, ERR_GUILD_PERMISSIONS);
1616 else if (Member* member = GetMember(name))
1617 {
1618 // Guild masters cannot be removed
1619 if (member->IsRank(GR_GUILDMASTER))
1620 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_REMOVE, ERR_GUILD_LEADER_LEAVE);
1621 // Do not allow to remove player with the same rank or higher
1622 else
1623 {
1624 Member const* memberMe = GetMember(player->GetGUID());
1625 if (!memberMe || member->IsRankNotLower(memberMe->GetRankId()))
1626 SendCommandResult(session, GUILD_COMMAND_REMOVE, ERR_GUILD_RANK_TOO_HIGH_S, name);
1627 else
1628 {
1629 ObjectGuid guid = member->GetGUID();
1630 // After call to DeleteMember pointer to member becomes invalid
1631 DeleteMember(guid, false, true);
1632 _LogEvent(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_UNINVITE_PLAYER, player->GetGUID().GetCounter(), guid.GetCounter());
1633 _BroadcastEvent(GE_REMOVED, ObjectGuid::Empty, name.c_str(), player->GetName().c_str());
1634 }
1635 }
1636 }

1638
1639void Guild::HandleUpdateMemberRank(WorldSession* session, std::string const& name, bool demote)
1640{
1641 Player* player = session->GetPlayer();
1642 GuildCommandType type = demote ? GUILD_COMMAND_DEMOTE : GUILD_COMMAND_PROMOTE;
1643 // Player must have rights to promote
1644 if (!_HasRankRight(player, demote ? GR_RIGHT_DEMOTE : GR_RIGHT_PROMOTE))
1645 SendCommandResult(session, type, ERR_GUILD_PERMISSIONS);
1646 // Promoted player must be a member of guild
1647 else if (Member* member = GetMember(name))
1648 {
1649 // Player cannot promote himself
1650 if (member->IsSamePlayer(player->GetGUID()))
1651 {
1652 SendCommandResult(session, type, ERR_GUILD_NAME_INVALID);
1653 return;
1654 }
1655
1656 Member const* memberMe = GetMember(player->GetGUID());
1657 uint8 rankId = memberMe->GetRankId();
1658 if (demote)
1659 {
1660 // Player can demote only lower rank members
1661 if (member->IsRankNotLower(rankId))
1662 {
1663 SendCommandResult(session, type, ERR_GUILD_RANK_TOO_HIGH_S, name);
1664 return;
1665 }
1666 // Lowest rank cannot be demoted
1667 if (member->GetRankId() >= _GetLowestRankId())
1668 {
1669 SendCommandResult(session, type, ERR_GUILD_RANK_TOO_LOW_S, name);
1670 return;
1671 }
1672 }
1673 else
1674 {
1675 // Allow to promote only to lower rank than member's rank
1676 // member->GetRankId() + 1 is the highest rank that current player can promote to
1677 if (member->IsRankNotLower(rankId + 1))
1678 {
1679 SendCommandResult(session, type, ERR_GUILD_RANK_TOO_HIGH_S, name);
1680 return;
1681 }
1682 }
1683
1684 uint32 newRankId = member->GetRankId() + (demote ? 1 : -1);
1685 member->ChangeRank(newRankId);
1686 _LogEvent(demote ? GUILD_EVENT_LOG_DEMOTE_PLAYER : GUILD_EVENT_LOG_PROMOTE_PLAYER, player->GetGUID().GetCounter(), member->GetGUID().GetCounter(), newRankId);
1687 _BroadcastEvent(demote ? GE_DEMOTION : GE_PROMOTION, ObjectGuid::Empty, player->GetName().c_str(), name.c_str(), _GetRankName(newRankId).c_str());
1688 }
1689}

1712void Guild::HandleRemoveRank(WorldSession* session, uint8 rankId)
1713{
1714 // Cannot remove rank if total count is minimum allowed by the client or is not leader
1715 if (_GetRanksSize() <= GUILD_RANKS_MIN_COUNT || rankId >= _GetRanksSize() || !_IsLeader(session->GetPlayer()))
1716 return;
1717
1718 // Delete bank rights for rank
1719 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_BANK_RIGHTS_FOR_RANK);
1720 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1721 stmt->setUInt8(1, rankId);
1722 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
1723 // Delete rank
1724 stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_DEL_GUILD_LOWEST_RANK);
1725 stmt->setUInt32(0, m_id);
1726 stmt->setUInt8(1, rankId);
1727 CharacterDatabase.Execute(stmt);
1728
1729 m_ranks.pop_back();
1730
1731 _BroadcastEvent(GE_RANK_DELETED, ObjectGuid::Empty, std::to_string(rankId).c_str());
1732}

1734void Guild::HandleMemberDepositMoney(WorldSession* session, uint32 amount)
1735{
1736 Player* player = session->GetPlayer();
1737
1738 // Call script after validation and before money transfer.
1739 sScriptMgr->OnGuildMemberDepositMoney(this, player, amount);
1740
1741 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
1742 _ModifyBankMoney(trans, amount, true);
1743
1744 player->ModifyMoney(-int32(amount));
1745 player->SaveGoldToDB(trans);
1746 _LogBankEvent(trans, GUILD_BANK_LOG_DEPOSIT_MONEY, uint8(0), player->GetGUID().GetCounter(), amount);
1747

1750 std::string aux = ByteArrayToHexStr(reinterpret_cast<uint8*>(&m_bankMoney), 8, true);
1751 _BroadcastEvent(GE_BANK_MONEY_SET, ObjectGuid::Empty, aux.c_str());

1754 {
1755 sLog->outCommand(player->GetSession()->GetAccountId(),
1756 "GM %s (Account: %u) deposit money (Amount: %u) to guild bank (Guild ID %u)",

1760
1761bool Guild::HandleMemberWithdrawMoney(WorldSession* session, uint32 amount, bool repair)
1762{
1763 //clamp amount to MAX_MONEY_AMOUNT, Players can't hold more than that anyway
1764 amount = std::min(amount, MAX_MONEY_AMOUNT);
1765
1766 if (m_bankMoney < amount) // Not enough money in bank
1767 return false;
1768
1769 Player* player = session->GetPlayer();
1770
1771 Member* member = GetMember(player->GetGUID());
1772 if (!member)
1773 return false;
1774
1775 if (uint32(_GetMemberRemainingMoney(member)) < amount) // Check if we have enough slot/money today
1776 return false;
1777
1778 // Call script after validation and before money transfer.
1779 sScriptMgr->OnGuildMemberWitdrawMoney(this, player, amount, repair);
1780
1781 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
1782 // Add money to player (if required)
1783 if (!repair)
1784 {
1785 if (!player->ModifyMoney(amount))
1786 return false;
1787
1788 player->SaveGoldToDB(trans);
1789 }
1790
1791 // Update remaining money amount
1792 member->UpdateBankWithdrawValue(trans, GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS, amount);
1793 // Remove money from bank
1794 _ModifyBankMoney(trans, amount, false);
1795
1796 // Log guild bank event
1797 _LogBankEvent(trans, repair ? GUILD_BANK_LOG_REPAIR_MONEY : GUILD_BANK_LOG_WITHDRAW_MONEY, uint8(0), player->GetGUID().GetCounter(), amount);
1798 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
1799
1800 std::string aux = ByteArrayToHexStr(reinterpret_cast<uint8*>(&m_bankMoney), 8, true);
1801 _BroadcastEvent(GE_BANK_MONEY_SET, ObjectGuid::Empty, aux.c_str());
1802 return true;
1803}

1914}

1941bool Guild::LoadFromDB(Field* fields)
1942{

1959
1960 _CreateLogHolders();
1961 return true;
1962}

2073// Validates guild data loaded from database. Returns false if guild should be deleted.
2074bool Guild::Validate()
2075{
2076 // Validate ranks data
2077 // GUILD RANKS represent a sequence starting from 0 = GUILD_MASTER (ALL PRIVILEGES) to max 9 (lowest privileges).
2078 // The lower rank id is considered higher rank - so promotion does rank-- and demotion does rank++
2079 // Between ranks in sequence cannot be gaps - so 0, 1, 2, 4 is impossible
2080 // Min ranks count is 5 and max is 10.
2081 bool broken_ranks = false;
2082 uint8 ranks = _GetRanksSize();
2083 if (ranks < GUILD_RANKS_MIN_COUNT || ranks > GUILD_RANKS_MAX_COUNT)
2084 {
2085 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "Guild %u has invalid number of ranks, creating new...", m_id);
2086 broken_ranks = true;
2087 }
2088 else
2089 {
2090 for (uint8 rankId = 0; rankId < ranks; ++rankId)
2091 {
2092 RankInfo* rankInfo = GetRankInfo(rankId);
2093 if (rankInfo->GetId() != rankId)
2094 {
2095 TC_LOG_ERROR("guild", "Guild %u has broken rank id %u, creating default set of ranks...", m_id, rankId);
2096 broken_ranks = true;
2097 }
2098 else
2099 {
2100 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
2101 rankInfo->CreateMissingTabsIfNeeded(_GetPurchasedTabsSize(), trans, true);
2102 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
2103 }
2104 }
2105 }
2106
2107 if (broken_ranks)
2108 {
2109 m_ranks.clear();
2110 _CreateDefaultGuildRanks(DEFAULT_LOCALE);
2111 }
2112
2113 // Validate members' data
2114 for (Members::iterator itr = m_members.begin(); itr != m_members.end(); ++itr)
2115 if (itr->second->GetRankId() > _GetRanksSize())
2116 itr->second->ChangeRank(_GetLowestRankId());
2117
2118 // Repair the structure of the guild.
2119 // If the guildmaster doesn't exist or isn't member of the guild
2120 // attempt to promote another member.
2121 Member* pLeader = GetMember(m_leaderGuid);
2122 if (!pLeader)
2123 {
2124 DeleteMember(m_leaderGuid);
2125 // If no more members left, disband guild
2126 if (m_members.empty())
2127 {
2128 Disband();
2129 return false;
2130 }
2131 }
2132 else if (!pLeader->IsRank(GR_GUILDMASTER))
2133 _SetLeaderGUID(pLeader);
2134
2135 // Check config if multiple guildmasters are allowed
2136 if (!sConfigMgr->GetBoolDefault("Guild.AllowMultipleGuildMaster", 0))
2137 for (Members::iterator itr = m_members.begin(); itr != m_members.end(); ++itr)
2138 if (itr->second->GetRankId() == GR_GUILDMASTER && !itr->second->IsSamePlayer(m_leaderGuid))
2139 itr->second->ChangeRank(GR_OFFICER);
2140
2141 _UpdateAccountsNumber();
2142 return true;
2143}

2200 }

2208// Members handling
2209bool Guild::AddMember(ObjectGuid guid, uint8 rankId)
2210{
2211 Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(guid);
2212 // Player cannot be in guild
2213 if (player)
2214 {
2215 if (player->GetGuildId() != 0)
2216 return false;
2217 }
2218 else if (Player::GetGuildIdFromDB(guid) != 0)
2219 return false;
2220
2221 // Remove all player signs from another petitions
2222 // This will be prevent attempt to join many guilds and corrupt guild data integrity
2223 Player::RemovePetitionsAndSigns(guid, GUILD_CHARTER_TYPE);
2224
2225 ObjectGuid::LowType lowguid = guid.GetCounter();
2226
2227 // If rank was not passed, assign lowest possible rank
2228 if (rankId == GUILD_RANK_NONE)
2229 rankId = _GetLowestRankId();
2230
2231 Member* member = new Member(m_id, guid, rankId);
2232 std::string name;
2233 if (player)
2234 {
2235 m_members[lowguid] = member;
2236 player->SetInGuild(m_id);
2237 player->SetGuildIdInvited(0);
2238 player->SetRank(rankId);
2239 member->SetStats(player);
2240 SendLoginInfo(player->GetSession());
2241 name = player->GetName();
2242 }
2243 else
2244 {
2245 member->ResetFlags();
2246
2247 bool ok = false;
2248 // Player must exist
2249 PreparedStatement* stmt = CharacterDatabase.GetPreparedStatement(CHAR_SEL_CHAR_DATA_FOR_GUILD);
2250 stmt->setUInt32(0, lowguid);
2251 if (PreparedQueryResult result = CharacterDatabase.Query(stmt))
2252 {
2253 Field* fields = result->Fetch();
2254 name = fields[0].GetString();
2255 member->SetStats(
2256 name,
2257 fields[1].GetUInt8(),
2258 fields[2].GetUInt8(),
2259 fields[3].GetUInt16(),
2260 fields[4].GetUInt32());
2261
2262 ok = member->CheckStats();
2263 }
2264 if (!ok)
2265 {
2266 delete member;
2267 return false;
2268 }
2269 m_members[lowguid] = member;
2270 }
2271
2272 SQLTransaction trans(NULL);
2273 member->SaveToDB(trans);
2274
2275 _UpdateAccountsNumber();
2276 _LogEvent(GUILD_EVENT_LOG_JOIN_GUILD, lowguid);
2277 _BroadcastEvent(GE_JOINED, guid, name.c_str());
2278
2279 // Call scripts if member was succesfully added (and stored to database)
2280 sScriptMgr->OnGuildAddMember(this, player, rankId);
2281
2282 return true;
2283}
2284
2285void Guild::DeleteMember(ObjectGuid guid, bool isDisbanding, bool isKicked, bool canDeleteGuild)
2286{
2287 ObjectGuid::LowType lowguid = guid.GetCounter();
2288 Player* player = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(guid);
2289
2290 // Guild master can be deleted when loading guild and guid doesn't exist in characters table
2291 // or when he is removed from guild by gm command
2292 if (m_leaderGuid == guid && !isDisbanding)
2293 {
2294 Member* oldLeader = NULL;
2295 Member* newLeader = NULL;
2296 for (Guild::Members::iterator i = m_members.begin(); i != m_members.end(); ++i)
2297 {
2298 if (i->first == lowguid)
2299 oldLeader = i->second;
2300 else if (!newLeader || newLeader->GetRankId() > i->second->GetRankId())
2301 newLeader = i->second;
2302 }
2303
2304 if (!newLeader)
2305 {
2306 Disband();
2307 if (canDeleteGuild)
2308 delete this;
2309 return;
2310 }
2311
2312 _SetLeaderGUID(newLeader);
2313
2314 // If player not online data in data field will be loaded from guild tabs no need to update it !!
2315 if (Player* newLeaderPlayer = newLeader->FindPlayer())
2316 newLeaderPlayer->SetRank(GR_GUILDMASTER);
2317
2318 // If leader does not exist (at guild loading with deleted leader) do not send broadcasts
2319 if (oldLeader)
2320 {
2321 _BroadcastEvent(GE_LEADER_CHANGED, ObjectGuid::Empty, oldLeader->GetName().c_str(), newLeader->GetName().c_str());
2322 _BroadcastEvent(GE_LEFT, guid, oldLeader->GetName().c_str());
2323 }
2324 }
2325 // Call script on remove before member is actually removed from guild (and database)
2326 sScriptMgr->OnGuildRemoveMember(this, player, isDisbanding, isKicked);
2327
2328 if (Member* member = GetMember(guid))
2329 delete member;
2330 m_members.erase(lowguid);
2331
2332 // If player not online data in data field will be loaded from guild tabs no need to update it !!
2333 if (player)
2334 {
2335 player->SetInGuild(0);
2336 player->SetRank(0);
2337 }
2338
2339 _DeleteMemberFromDB(lowguid);
2340 if (!isDisbanding)
2341 _UpdateAccountsNumber();
2342}

2579inline int32 Guild::_GetMemberRemainingSlots(Member const* member, uint8 tabId) const
2580{

2582 {
2583 uint8 rankId = member->GetRankId();
2584 if (rankId == GR_GUILDMASTER)
2585 return static_cast<int32>(GUILD_WITHDRAW_SLOT_UNLIMITED);
2586 if ((_GetRankBankTabRights(rankId, tabId) & GUILD_BANK_RIGHT_VIEW_TAB) != 0)
2587 {
2588 int32 remaining = _GetRankBankTabSlotsPerDay(rankId, tabId) - member->GetBankWithdrawValue(tabId);

2591 }
2592 }

2648void Guild::_LogBankEvent(SQLTransaction& trans, GuildBankEventLogTypes eventType, uint8 tabId, ObjectGuid::LowType lowguid, uint32 itemOrMoney, uint16 itemStackCount, uint8 destTabId)
2649{
2650 if (tabId > GUILD_BANK_MAX_TABS)
2651 return;

2663 LogHolder* pLog = m_bankEventLog[tabId];
2664 pLog->AddEvent(trans, new BankEventLogEntry(m_id, pLog->GetNextGUID(), eventType, dbTabId, lowguid, itemOrMoney, itemStackCount, destTabId));
2665
2666 sScriptMgr->OnGuildBankEvent(this, uint8(eventType), tabId, lowguid, itemOrMoney, itemStackCount, destTabId);

2682void Guild::_MoveItems(MoveItemData* pSrc, MoveItemData* pDest, uint32 splitedAmount)
2683{
2684 // 1. Initialize source item
2685 if (!pSrc->InitItem())
2686 return; // No source item
2687
2688 // 2. Check source item
2689 if (!pSrc->CheckItem(splitedAmount))
2690 return; // Source item or splited amount is invalid
2691 /*
2692 if (pItemSrc->GetCount() == 0)
2693 {
2694 TC_LOG_FATAL("guild", "Guild::SwapItems: Player %s(GUIDLow: %u) tried to move item %u from tab %u slot %u to tab %u slot %u, but item %u has a stack of zero!",
2695 player->GetName(), player->GetGUID().GetCounter(), pItemSrc->GetEntry(), tabId, slotId, destTabId, destSlotId, pItemSrc->GetEntry());
2696 //return; // Commented out for now, uncomment when it's verified that this causes a crash!!
2697 }
2698 // */
2699
2700 // 3. Check destination rights
2701 if (!pDest->HasStoreRights(pSrc))
2702 return; // Player has no rights to store item in destination
2703
2704 // 4. Check source withdraw rights
2705 if (!pSrc->HasWithdrawRights(pDest))
2706 return; // Player has no rights to withdraw items from source
2707
2708 // 5. Check split
2709 if (splitedAmount)
2710 {
2711 // 5.1. Clone source item
2712 if (!pSrc->CloneItem(splitedAmount))
2713 return; // Item could not be cloned
2714
2715 // 5.2. Move splited item to destination
2716 _DoItemsMove(pSrc, pDest, true, splitedAmount);
2717 }
2718 else // 6. No split
2719 {
2720 // 6.1. Try to merge items in destination (pDest->GetItem() == NULL)
2721 if (!_DoItemsMove(pSrc, pDest, false)) // Item could not be merged
2722 {
2723 // 6.2. Try to swap items
2724 // 6.2.1. Initialize destination item
2725 if (!pDest->InitItem())
2726 return;
2727
2728 // 6.2.2. Check rights to store item in source (opposite direction)
2729 if (!pSrc->HasStoreRights(pDest))
2730 return; // Player has no rights to store item in source (opposite direction)
2731
2732 if (!pDest->HasWithdrawRights(pSrc))
2733 return; // Player has no rights to withdraw item from destination (opposite direction)
2734
2735 // 6.2.3. Swap items (pDest->GetItem() != NULL)
2736 _DoItemsMove(pSrc, pDest, true);
2737 }
2738 }
2739 // 7. Send changes
2740 _SendBankContentUpdate(pSrc, pDest);
2741}
2742
2743bool Guild::_DoItemsMove(MoveItemData* pSrc, MoveItemData* pDest, bool sendError, uint32 splitedAmount)
2744{
2745 Item* pDestItem = pDest->GetItem();
2746 bool swap = (pDestItem != NULL);
2747
2748 Item* pSrcItem = pSrc->GetItem(splitedAmount != 0);
2749 // 1. Can store source item in destination
2750 if (!pDest->CanStore(pSrcItem, swap, sendError))
2751 return false;
2752
2753 // 2. Can store destination item in source
2754 if (swap)
2755 if (!pSrc->CanStore(pDestItem, true, true))
2756 return false;
2757
2758 // GM LOG (@todo move to scripts)
2759 pDest->LogAction(pSrc);
2760 if (swap)
2761 pSrc->LogAction(pDest);
2762
2763 SQLTransaction trans = CharacterDatabase.BeginTransaction();
2764 // 3. Log bank events
2765 pDest->LogBankEvent(trans, pSrc, pSrcItem->GetCount());
2766 if (swap)
2767 pSrc->LogBankEvent(trans, pDest, pDestItem->GetCount());
2768
2769 // 4. Remove item from source
2770 pSrc->RemoveItem(trans, pDest, splitedAmount);
2771
2772 // 5. Remove item from destination
2773 if (swap)
2774 pDest->RemoveItem(trans, pSrc);
2775
2776 // 6. Store item in destination
2777 pDest->StoreItem(trans, pSrcItem);
2778
2779 // 7. Store item in source
2780 if (swap)
2781 pSrc->StoreItem(trans, pDestItem);
2782
2783 CharacterDatabase.CommitTransaction(trans);
2784 return true;
2785}

2800
2801void Guild::_SendBankContentUpdate(MoveItemData* pSrc, MoveItemData* pDest) const
2802{
2803 ASSERT(pSrc->IsBank() || pDest->IsBank());
2804
2805 uint8 tabId = 0;
2806 SlotIds slots;
2807 if (pSrc->IsBank()) // B ->
2808 {
2809 tabId = pSrc->GetContainer();
2810 slots.insert(pSrc->GetSlotId());
2811 if (pDest->IsBank()) // B -> B
2812 {
2813 // Same tab - add destination slots to collection
2814 if (pDest->GetContainer() == pSrc->GetContainer())
2815 pDest->CopySlots(slots);
2816 else // Different tabs - send second message
2817 {
2818 SlotIds destSlots;
2819 pDest->CopySlots(destSlots);
2820 _SendBankContentUpdate(pDest->GetContainer(), destSlots);
2821 }
2822 }
2823 }
2824 else if (pDest->IsBank()) // C -> B
2825 {
2826 tabId = pDest->GetContainer();
2827 pDest->CopySlots(slots);
2828 }
2829
2830 _SendBankContentUpdate(tabId, slots);
2831}

2838void Guild::_BroadcastEvent(GuildEvents guildEvent, ObjectGuid guid, const char* param1, const char* param2, const char* param3) const
2839{
2840 uint8 count = !param3 ? (!param2 ? (!param1 ? 0 : 1) : 2) : 3;
2841
2842 WorldPacket data(SMSG_GUILD_EVENT, 1 + 1 + count + (guid ? 8 : 0));
2843 data << uint8(guildEvent);
2844 data << uint8(count);
2845
2846 if (param3)
2847 data << param1 << param2 << param3;
2848 else if (param2)
2849 data << param1 << param2;
2850 else if (param1)
2851 data << param1;
2852
2853 if (guid)
2854 data << uint64(guid);
2855
2856 BroadcastPacket(&data);
2857
2858 if (sLog->ShouldLog("guild", LOG_LEVEL_DEBUG))
2859 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "SMSG_GUILD_EVENT [Broadcast] Event: %s (%u)", _GetGuildEventString(guildEvent).c_str(), guildEvent);
2860}

2862void Guild::_SendBankList(WorldSession* session /* = NULL*/, uint8 tabId /*= 0*/, bool sendAllSlots /*= false*/, SlotIds *slots /*= NULL*/) const
2863{
2864 WorldPacket data(SMSG_GUILD_BANK_LIST, 500);
2865 data << uint64(m_bankMoney);
2866 data << uint8(tabId);
2867 size_t rempos = data.wpos();
2868 data << uint32(0);
2869 data << uint8(sendAllSlots);
2870
2871 if (sendAllSlots && !tabId)
2872 {
2873 data << uint8(_GetPurchasedTabsSize()); // Number of tabs
2874 for (uint8 i = 0; i < _GetPurchasedTabsSize(); ++i)
2875 m_bankTabs[i]->WriteInfoPacket(data);
2876 }
2877
2878 BankTab const* tab = GetBankTab(tabId);
2879 if (!tab)
2880 data << uint8(0);
2881 else if (sendAllSlots)
2882 tab->WritePacket(data);
2883 else if (slots && !slots->empty())
2884 {
2885 data << uint8(slots->size());
2886 for (SlotIds::const_iterator itr = slots->begin(); itr != slots->end(); ++itr)
2887 tab->WriteSlotPacket(data, *itr, false);
2888 }
2889 else
2890 data << uint8(0);
2891
2892 if (session)
2893 {
2894 int32 numSlots = 0;
2895 if (Member const* member = GetMember(session->GetPlayer()->GetGUID()))
2896 numSlots = _GetMemberRemainingSlots(member, tabId);
2897 data.put<uint32>(rempos, numSlots);
2898 session->SendPacket(&data);
2899 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "SMSG_GUILD_BANK_LIST [%s]: TabId: %u, FullSlots: %u, slots: %d",
2900 session->GetPlayerInfo().c_str(), tabId, sendAllSlots, numSlots);
2901 }
2902 else /// @todo - Probably this is just sent to session + those that have sent CMSG_GUILD_BANKER_ACTIVATE
2903 {
2904 for (Members::const_iterator itr = m_members.begin(); itr != m_members.end(); ++itr)
2905 {
2906 if (!_MemberHasTabRights(itr->second->GetGUID(), tabId, GUILD_BANK_RIGHT_VIEW_TAB))
2907 continue;
2908 Player* player = itr->second->FindPlayer();
2909 if (!player)
2910 continue;
2911
2912 uint32 numSlots = _GetMemberRemainingSlots(itr->second, tabId);
2913 data.put<uint32>(rempos, numSlots);
2914 player->GetSession()->SendPacket(&data);
2915 TC_LOG_DEBUG("guild", "SMSG_GUILD_BANK_LIST [%s]: TabId: %u, FullSlots: %u, slots: %u"
2916 , player->GetName().c_str(), tabId, sendAllSlots, numSlots);
2917 }
2918 }
2919}
